**Greta Jiehan Lee** (born March 7, 1983) is an American actress. She is best known for starring as Maxine in the [Netflix](Netflix) comedy-drama series *[Doll](Russian)(Russian Doll (TV series))* and for her role in the second season of [TV+](Apple)(Apple TV+) drama series *[Morning Show](The)(The Morning Show (American TV series))*.

She gained wider recognition for her role as Nora in the 2023 film *[Lives](Past)(Past Lives (film))*.

## Early life

Lee was born and raised in [Angeles](Los)(Los Angeles), [California](California). Her parents are [Korean](Koreans) immigrants.

While attending [School](Harvard-Westlake)(Harvard-Westlake School), she became interested in the performing arts. After high school, she studied communication and theater at [University](Northwestern)(Northwestern University). She then moved to New York City to pursue acting.

## Career

Lee made her Broadway debut in 2007 as high-achieving, multilingual honor student Marcy Park (replacement) in *[25th Annual Putnam County Spelling Bee](The)(The 25th Annual Putnam County Spelling Bee)* and in 2010, appeared in *[Bête](La)(La Bête (play))* as Dorine. IBDB |url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-cast-staff/greta-lee-457802 |access-date=2023-02-23 |website=www.ibdb.com}} She has played Soojin in *[Girls](Girls (TV series))* and Homeless Heidi in *[Maintenance](High)(High Maintenance)*. She was a guest star in the TV shows *[Girl](New)(New Girl)* and *[Pines](Wayward)(Wayward Pines)*. She costarred as Hae Won in *[Sisters](Sisters (2015 film))* alongside [Fey](Tina)(Tina Fey) and [Poehler](Amy)(Amy Poehler). Lee starred as Maxine in the [Netflix](Netflix) comedy-drama series *[Doll](Russian)(Russian Doll (TV series))* and as Stella Bak in the [TV+](Apple)(Apple TV+) drama series *[Morning Show](The)(The Morning Show (American TV series))*. She voiced Lyla in a [scene](post-credits)(post-credits scene) of the animated film *[Into the Spider-verse](Spider-Man:)(Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse),* and returned in the 2023 sequel, [Across the Spider-verse*](*Spider-Man:)(Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse). Lee also starred as Nora in the 2023 film *[Lives](Past)(Past Lives (film))*.

## Personal life

Lee is married to Russ Armstrong, She's Funny That Way |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130134518/https://tidal-mag.com/magazine/shes-funny-that-way |access-date=2023-02-09 |website=web.archive.org}} with whom she has two sons.
